
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `autopoint` baraye update kardane file-haye gettext estefade mishavad. Gettext baraye tarjome kardan barnamye shoma be zabanhaye mokhtalef be kar miravad. `autopoint` komak mikonad ke shoma file-haye `po` va `pot` khod ra ba akharin standard-ha va taghirat be rooz negah دارید.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--force` --> 💪 Be zor update mikonad, hata agar moshkelati bashad.
    🔹 `--verbose` --> 🗣️ Etela'ate bishtari dar morede chigonegi kar kardane dastoor chap mikonad.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Version-e `autopoint` ra neshon midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ autopoint

    🔹 File-haye gettext ra dar directory kari be rooz mikonad.

    $ autopoint --force

    🔹 File-haye gettext ra be zor be rooz mikonad, hata agar error bashad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ autopoint
    Looking for '[gettext]' in 'configure.ac'... found.
    ...
    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, `autopoint` configure.ac ra migardad va file-haye gettext-e shoma ra be rooz mikonad ta barnameye shoma betone be zabanhaye digar tarjome shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `autopoint` command is used to update gettext infrastructure files. Gettext is used for internationalizing your programs, allowing them to be translated into different languages. `autopoint` helps you keep your `po` and `pot` files up-to-date with the latest standards and changes.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--force` --> 💪 Force updates, even if there are potential problems.
    🔹 `--verbose` --> 🗣️ Print more information about how the command is working.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Display the version of `autopoint`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ autopoint

    🔹 Updates gettext files in the current directory.

    $ autopoint --force

    🔹 Forces the update of gettext files, even if there are errors.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ autopoint
    Looking for '[gettext]' in 'configure.ac'... found.
    ...
    🔹 By running this command, `autopoint` searches `configure.ac` and updates your gettext files, allowing your program to be translated into other languages.
